Executive Profile
Matthew Adam Drapkin J.D.Co-Founder, Chief Executive Officer, and Portfolio Manager, Northern Right Capital Management, L.P.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships44--
Background

		Mr. Matthew Adam Drapkin, also known as Matt, J.D., is a Co-Founder, Chief Executive Officer and Portfolio Manager at Northern Right Capital Management, L.P. Mr. Drapkin joined Northern Right Capital in December 2009. Prior to this, he served as the Head of Research, Special Situations and Private Equity at Enso Capital Management LLC since March 2008. Mr. Drapkin served as General Manager of CondéNet, Inc. From January 2003 to March 2008, he worked at MacAndrews & Forbes ... Holdings, Inc. where he served as the Senior Vice President of Corporate Development from 2003 to 2008 and was responsible for sourcing, evaluating and executing investment opportunities. Prior to that, Mr. Drapkin served as the General Manager of several Conde Nast interest sites and an investment banker at Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. He has been a Director of Hot Topic Inc. since October 1, 2010 and its Lead Director since November 2011. He has been a Director at Great Elm Capital Group, Inc. since April 14, 2017. He has been an Independent Director at Intevac Inc., since December 2013. Mr. Drapkin has been Director of PRGX Global, Inc. since November 11, 2016. He has been Independent Director of Edmentum, Inc. since March 18, 2009. Mr. Drapkin served as an Independent Director at Xura, Inc. since March 12, 2014 until August 19, 2016. He served as the Chairman of Ruby Tuesday, Inc., from December 1, 2012 to October 27, 2013, its Independent Director from June 30, 2011 to October 27, 2013 and as the Lead Director from July 25, 2012 to December 1, 2012. Mr. Drapkin served as a Director at Glu Mobile, Inc. from May 2010 to April 11, 2013 and Alloy Inc., until April 15, 2010. Mr. Drapkin served as Director at Plato Learning, Inc. He holds a J.D. from School Of Law, Columbia University, a Master of Business Administration in Finance from Columbia Business School and a B.A. in American History from Princeton University.Read Full Background




